Description: Blue feldspar scarab, elytra marked, feathered legs, longitudinally pierced, base inscribed with the name of the priestess Senusret(?) surrounded by scrolls.
Curator's comments: Martin, Egyptian Admin and Private-name Seals (1971) cat no.438 [pl.1.17].
Bibliographic references: Martin 1971 / Egyptian administrative and private-name seals, principally of the Middle Kingdom and Second Intermediate Period (438)
